-- Ind-Barath Power Infra Seeks to Raise 11.4 Billion Rupees in Initial Sale
-- Ruth David
-- 2010-06-22T08:53:05Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-22/ind-barath-power-infra-seeks-to-raise-11-4-billion-rupees-in-initial-sale.html

          
          
             Ind-Barath Power Infra Ltd. plans to
raise 11.4 billion rupees ($248 million) from an initial public
offering in India.  
 The sale will be managed by JM Financial Consultants Pvt.,
Motilal Oswal Investment Advisors Pvt., Bank of America Corp.,
IDFC Capital Ltd. and Avendus Capital Pvt., according to a draft
offer document on JM Financialâ€™s website.  
 Stakeholders including CVCIGP II Client Rosehill Ltd. and
Unit Trust of India will sell an additional 6.47 million shares,
the document showed.  
